# React Component Conventions

## File structure

- One component per file. File name matches component name.
- Colocate `.scss` with `.tsx` in the same directory.
- Feature components go in `src/features/feature-name/`.
- Page components go in `src/pages/page-name/`.
- Reusable UI goes in `src/library/`.

## Component patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Named export for components
export function MyComponent({ title }: Props) { ... }

// ✅ Also acceptable
export const MyComponent: React.FC<Props> = ({ title }) => { ... }
```

## Library components — use what exists

Use existing library components instead of raw HTML:

- `<Col>` / `<Row>` for flex layout (not raw `div` with `display: flex`)
- `<Card>` for elevated content containers
- `<Button>` / `<IconButton>` for actions
- `<Input>`, `<PillSelect>`, `<Dropdown>`, `<DatePicker>` for form controls
- `<Badge>` for status labels
- `<TabGroup>` for tabbed content
- `<PageContainer>` + `<PageHeader>` for page layout

## Styling

- Use SCSS files colocated with the component, not inline styles.
- Exception: dynamic values that depend on props/state can use `style={}`.
- Import palette tokens in SCSS — never hardcode colors/spacing.

## Icons

Use FontAwesome via `@fortawesome/react-fontawesome`. Import from `free-solid-svg-icons`, `free-regular-svg-icons`, or `free-brands-svg-icons`.

## Theme

Access dark mode via `useDarkModeSelector()` from `~src/theme-slice`. In SCSS, use the `.dark-mode` parent selector pattern.
